cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with stereo matching and depth estimation from images captured by two cameras with different field of views. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions the practical application of the proposed method in synthesizing the Bokeh effect, which can be useful in robotics applications. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes deep learning solutions for the TW-SM problem. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper proposes an end-to-end deep multitask neural network for TW-SM. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the synthesis of the Bokeh effect, which is a graphics-related task.
